## ObjectType type

A type-validator/-parser that validates or parses object-like type `ResultType`<!-- -->.

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
export declare type ObjectType<ResultType, TypeConfig = unknown> = TypeImpl<BaseObjectLikeTypeImpl<ResultType, TypeConfig>>;
```

<b>References:</b> [TypeImpl](./types.typeimpl.md)<!-- -->, [BaseObjectLikeTypeImpl](./types.baseobjectliketypeimpl.md)

## Remarks

This is the most generic interface that describes an object-like type. It does not provide access to type-specific utilities / properties. Use [TypeImpl](./types.typeimpl.md) for an interface that describes the actual Type implementation. Use `Type<ResultType>` to also allow scalar values for `ResultType`<!-- -->.
